Subject: Re: [T2] Ignition OFF=Lights ON??

On Wed, 16 Apr 2003, John Baker wrote:

> I am working on a 72 deluxe that has been sitting in a
> barn yard for about 3 years. A strange thing is that
> the headlights will only come ON when the ignition
> switch is turned to the OFF position, obviously it
> should be exactly the opposite, the lights should come
> on only when the ignition switch is on. So, is
> something wired backwards? Is it likely a headlight
> switch problem, an ignition switch problem, or bad wiring??

There _is_ a wire coming from the ignition switch that is hot only when
the key is off.  If the switch has been replaced it might have been
miswired.

